==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A word used to indicate [[clearance]], normally in relation to a [[ship]] proceeding into [[port]] from the 16th century onwards. The letter Q (Quebec) in the NATO maritime flags which is a yellow flag indicates that the vessel is in good health and wishs free pratique (passage) into a port. Normally after complying with the local health and quarantine regulations. It is an old French word practique which comes from Medieval Latin prctica (practic or pratticke) and originally the Greek word prktik (female) or prktikos (male) meaning [[practical]].

